[1]
Date: Tue 5 Jun 2007 12:42 PM CDT
Source: CBC News [edited]
<http://www.cbc.ca/canada/manitoba/story/2007/06/05/manitoba-anthrax.html>

Manitoba's 1st anthrax case of the year identified in cattle
------------------------------------------------------------
Anthrax caused the sudden death of an animal in south east Manitoba's Rural
Municipality of Stuartburn this spring, laboratory testing indicates. The
farm involved also had anthrax last summer [2006], Sandra Stevens, a
disease control specialist with the Canadian Food Inspection Agency (CFIA),
told CBC News.
Last year, an anthrax outbreak in Manitoba and Saskatchewan was the worst
in recent years. In Manitoba, between 14 Jul and 11 Oct 2006, anthrax
killed 148 livestock spread across 22 premises in 8 rural municipalities,
according to the CFIA website. In Saskatchewan, more than 800 animals died.
--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail rapporteur Brent Barrett
