[2]
From: Terry Whiting
Date: Fri 8 Jun 2007 8:00 AM

re: Manitoba's 1st anthrax case of the year identified in cattle
----------------------------------------------------------------
This particular beef herd is large for Manitoba at around 700 cattle of
various ages. It is also pastured in mixed woodland where the Canadian
Shield meets the Prairie.
They attempted a "herd" vaccination last year [2006] but the extended
family that owns these cattle had few farm records and really very little
knowledge on actually how many cattle were in the herd. Most of the cattle
(the ones they were able to catch) were vaccinated, but I could not
attribute this case to vaccine failure.
It is also a presumptive positive; it was PCR (polymerase chain reaction)
positive at both the provincial and the federal lab but was culture
negative. CFIA is proceeding with their assistance with the provision of
vaccine based on it is probably a true positive. I have cc'ed the local
CFIA vets on this message. If I am in substantive error they will correct
the detail.
--
