[I copied this report to Terry with a request for clarification before
posting, so I am very grateful for his replying with more information and
clarification. It seems clear that we are going to get more reported
outbreaks this summer in SK and MB if only from greater awareness, quite
apart from any residual ground contamination. Most Canadian ranchers are
sensible about spring (re)vaccinations but there is always a residue that
procrastinate and believe in the power of prayer. Such keep us busy.
Stuartburn is about 20 miles from the Canada/US border in the Roseau River
drainage, on Rt 201 equidistant between Hyws 12 and 59, and was in the
middle of last year's (2006) outbreaks. To find the town, go to
<http://www.mapquest.com/maps/> and enter Stuartburn. The province is MB
... The link is too long to include here. - Mod.MHJ]
